        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses the Duke of Argyll’s book [<hi rend="italic">Reign of law</hi> (1867)].</p> 
            <p>Cites his own views on diversity of structure and beauty.</p>
            <p>Encloses letter from Wallace. Sexual selection: evidence advanced by Wallace.</p>
            <p>Discusses correlation of growth.</p> 
<p>Comments on article in the <hi rend="italic">North British Review</hi> [by Fleeming Jenkin].</p> 
            <p>Discusses the evidence from physics on the age of the earth.</p>
            <p>[Four pages of the final letter are missing, but the draft is complete.]</p>
        </abstract>
